modules.description: This module provides functions for manipulating and analyzing abstract syntax trees (ASTs) with a focus on fragment dumping in different modes. It works primarily with AST nodes and supports operations like traversal, transformation, and comparison of code fragments. Concrete use cases include generating diffs between ASTs, extracting code snippets, and performing structural analysis in refactoring tools.

This module defines string values for version and copyright information. It provides direct access to these constants for use in documentation, logging, or compliance contexts. Useful for embedding and retrieving fixed metadata within an application.

This module defines a regular expression pattern for matching bar-separated strings and provides a function to extract paths from a given string by splitting it based on the pattern. It operates on strings and lists of strings, performing text parsing and path extraction. A concrete use case is processing colon-separated path strings commonly found in configuration or environment variables.

This module organizes functionality into three submodules focused on AST manipulation, string parsing, and version metadata. Astapi handles AST traversal, transformation, and comparison with use cases in refactoring and code diffing. Diffastapi parses bar-separated strings into paths, useful for processing environment variables and configuration strings. Version provides direct access to version and copyright strings for documentation and compliance purposes.
